A manager with steelproducer Krupp Stahl AG &lt;KRPG.F> was arrested yesterday forfraud and falsifying documents, the state prosecutor's officesaid today.    Two executives of steel trading companies in North RhineWestphalia and Hanover were also arrested for aiding the Kruppmanager, a spokesman for the office said. The office identifiedthe manager only as Alex I.    He said the manager is charged with faking signatures onforms ordering large shipments of heavy steel plate from one ofthe trading companies for which Krupp AG paid.    The spokesman said the manager ordered the shipments, whichon paper were for Krupp Stahl AG in Bochum but were deliveredto the trade house near Hanover.    The three men are also accused of pocketing profits fromthe sale of the steel plates, but both Krupp and theprosecutor's office declined comment on how much money wasinvolved.    The Hanover daily Hannoversche Allgemeine said in anarticle today the shipments' order value totalled 100 millionmarks, while another local daily, the Neue Presse, put thevalue at 50 million marks. REUTER&#3;